Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and high alkaline phosphatase, which may indicate possible hepatobiliary or bone involvement. Albumin is slightly elevated, and chloride and triglycerides are mildly increased. Total bilirubin is low but not clinically significant. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal and liver function.
